translated: Hagberg, Kjell Vilhel|m, pastor, Unnaryd, born July 8, 1906 in Sandseryd, Jönköp. County, son of kyrkoh. Emil H. and Agnes Bergh. Married in 1938 to Anna-Greta Klackenberg. Children: Gunnar b. 1940, Lars b. 1941, Birgitta b. 1943, Tomas b. 1946. He attended Stud:ex. in Jönköping in 1925, got his fil. kand. in Lund in 1928, his teol. kand. and passed his practical theology exam in 1931, and was ordained as a priest for Växjö diocese in 1932. He served as a sjöm:präst in Dunkirk and Calais, assistant vicar in Aringsås and acting kyrkoh. in Tävelsås, vicar in Tävelsås in 1936, military pastor in the Kronoberg regiment from 1941-1945, and kyrkoh. in S. Unnaryd from 1947. He was a part-time teacher at Växjö municipality's girls' school in 1938 and 1939. He served as a delegate for the diocesan council and sjöm:vården, and participated in the Poikn conference in April 1947. He wrote articles and sermons for newspapers and magazines.
